5 5 5  
5 5  
5  
>>> 

III. Pyramid Pattern - Right down mirror star Pattern

INPUT
n=int(input("enter number of rows:"))
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(i):
        print("",end=" ")
    for j in range(n-i):
        print("*",end=" ")
    print()

OUTPUT
Python 3.5.3 (v3.5.3:1880cb95a742, Jan 16 2017, 15:51:26) [MSC v.1900 32 bit (Intel)] on win32
Type "copyright", "credits" or "license()" for more information.
>>> 
================== RESTART: D:/sap/rightdown starpyramid.py ==================
enter number of rows:5
* * * * * 
 * * * * 
  * * * 
   * * 
    * 
>>> 

IV. Reversing a Number

INPUT
n=int(input("enter the number"))
num=n
sum=0
while(n>0):
    rem=n%10
    sum=(sum*10)+rem
    n=n//10
    print("reverse of a number:",sum)
    
OUTPUT
